class Solution {
public:
    long long minEnd(int n, int x) {
        long long ans = x;
        for (int i = 0; i < n - 1; i++) {
            ans = (ans << 1) | 1;
            if ((ans & x) == 0) {
                ans--;
            }
        }
        return ans;
    }
};
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The approach constructs the minimum possible value of nums[n-1] by maintaining a bitwise AND result of x. It iteratively shifts ans to the left and sets the least significant bit to 1. If the bitwise AND of ans and x becomes 0, it decrements ans to maintain the bitwise AND result of x.

